Job Description

The General Manager will support revenue growth by working with the secured Loan team on specific strategies to grow the loan finance business. You will play a key role in business development and expand on agencies/ resellers/ direct clients, with the vision and able to give strategic advice and expand markets.

Responsibilities:


Solicitation and expansion of mortgage loan finance business for the Company;
Actively competes in the market to increase sales growth;
Response for the profit & loss of the mortgage department through better risk management throughout the whole mortgage operation process;
Development business relationship with agencies, consultants, legal firms, surveyors, etc.;
Expand existing client relationships and build up different new clientele;
Drive the Secured Loan Team to develop new business opportunities to achieve business objectives;
Responsible for day-to-day client liaisons to understand the client’s latest financial needs and credit standings;
Provide consultation and analysis on clients’ financial and business needs. Design tailor-made financial solution to clients;
Structure the loan finance facilities and maintain a high quality of loan portfolio to exercise prudent credit assessment;
Manage daily business operations of the secured Loan Team in accordance with the Company's credit policies and guidelines;
Provide direction on problem loan handling, loan recovery and loan restructuring process of the delinquent accounts;
Collaborate with business partners including solicitors’ firm, property agents, collection agents and internal departments and perform regular quality assurance checks on borrower, business partners and credit processes to assure execution in accordance with prevailing policy and control standards;
To prepare regular or ad hoc management reports regarding the lending portfolio and credit compliance


Requirements:


Bachelor’s degree in finance, accounting, business management or equivalent;
At least 15 years’ solid experience in mortgage loan lending operation with at least 8 years in Money Lending Industrial;
Good knowledge in real estate industry;
Good people management skills, with solid experience in developing talents and achieving results through the team;
Good business connections with proven track record of success in growing a portfolio and in acquiring new businesses;
Sound credit and business experience in secured lending business and relevant clients / industrial network;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Detail-oriented and strong in risk management;
Self-motived, detail-minded, independent and service centric;
Proficient in both English and Chinese, written and verbal, including Putonghua

We offer competitive remuneration package, our benefits include:

Performance bonus
Education subsidy
Professional membership fee sponsorship
Life & medical insurance
Marriage Leave, Compassionate Leave, Examination Leave etc.
Public holidays
Staff purchase discount

Interested parties please send full resume with present and expected salary to Human Resources Department by clicking Apply Now.

