Interested parties, please send your FULL RESUME (in MS Word format) with availability, current and expected salary by email to Centaline Finance Limited.

Retail Lending Department (Job ID: 3110)



Responsibilities

To drive the business result and support business growth
To liaise with internal stakeholders and concerned business partners, including Call centre, Agency, etc.
To provide first-class customer service which meet the standards/requirements/guidelines prescribed by all concerned regulators as well as the Bank
To recommend products and services to meet the needs, risk profiles and affordability of customers whom will be provided with clear and accurate information and kept informed throughout and after the sales process
To plan marketing programs and new initiatives to achieve the Mortgage Loan business target
To develop the campaign logistics and work closely with internal departments to ensure effective and efficient implementation of planned initiatives
To prepare briefing notes to inform concerned Branches or colleagues for details of promotional offers, new initiatives, etc.
To monitor the result of promotional programmes and prepare programme result reports and post-program evaluation
To handle the marketing expense and ensure it worked within the budget
To ensure standardized practice in disclosing products and services information, features, risks, fees and charges to customers throughout and after the sales process

 Requirements

University graduate, preferably major in Marketing, Business, Finance or related disciplines OR Form 5 or above, with 5 subjects at Grade E or above in HKCEE including English, Chinese and Mathematics, AND
A minimum of 6 years’ banking experience.  Experience in Mortgage Product / marketing is preferred;
Proficient in project management, advertising production and direct marketing with strong communication skills;
Experienced in management of external direct sales or telesales agents would be a plus;
Possess effective interpersonal and presentation skills;
Independent, self-motivated and a team player;
Analytical with strong business acumen and problem-solving skills;
Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Proficiency in computer skills

Responsibilities:

Develop & implement strategies to ensure expectations from both the senior management and guests are met;
Develop and manage relationships with different business units;
Lead, define, develop and implement the operation strategic;
Maximize the profitability of the portfolio;
Evaluate the effectiveness and propose new ideas to strengthen the performance of operation;
Supervise whole business team to ensure strategic and project delivery under schedule.

Requirements:

Minimum 5-8 years of relevant experience in operation and project management;
Excellent leadership skills with a strong entrepreneurial spirit, self-motivated and constantly looking for new challenges;
Attention to detail, open minded, adaptable and collaborative;
Be innovative, positive and macroscopic in thinking;
Extensive knowledge of marketing strategies, channels, and branding will be preferred.
Related experience in mortgage is advantage.



Benefits:

Competitive salary package
Various caring leave types
Great learning and career development platform
Excellent working environment


Interested parties please send your CV (English and Chinese) with current and expected package, as well as date of availability to us for selection by clicking “Apply Now”. All information collected would be used for recruitment purpose only. Application process may take 2 to 3 weeks; candidates would not be considered, should there be no contact within 6 weeks.

Job Duties:

Assignment of daily operation to operators;
Perform checking & authorisation on Retail loans booking & disbursements, loan repayment & loan maintenance;
Preparing & checking of the Settlement calculation related to property discharge;
Arrangement in Facility setting & maintainence with fee collection;
Arranging & checking of external reportings on loans sold to external parties;
Co-ordinate with branch/ department staffs on customers requests.

Job Requirements:

Post-secondary or above.
At least 3 years of banking experience in loans processing, with 2 years supervisory level.
Familiar retail loans products such as mortgage and hire purchase loans.
Knowledge of PC operations and good typewriting skill in Chinese and English.
Good interpersonal communication skills.
Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese.



Interested parties, please click “Apply Now” for application.


